The paper proposes a new measure for text categorization, which falls under the sub-field of information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The measure involves term weighting, which is a common technique in machine learning and data mining, making computer science (cs) a likely category. The experimentation conducted on the 20 Newsgroups dataset suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and deep learning (cs.DL).
